# Pine Design System Rules

## 1. Project Overview

- React + TypeScript UI library
- Vanilla Extract (zero-runtime CSS), token-based theming
- @base-ui/react for accessibility, multiple themes (basic, game, crayon)
- Storybook + docs (Nextra) documentation

## 2. Project Structure

```
pine-ui-kit/
├── src/
│   ├── components/       # UI components (ComponentName/ folder)
│   ├── tokens/           # createThemeContract, theme definitions
│   └── providers/        # ThemeProvider
├── docs/                 # Nextra docs site
└── (storybook)
```

## 3. Component Pattern

- **Folder**: `src/components/ComponentName/`
- **Files**: `Component.tsx`, `Component.css.ts`, `Component.spec.tsx`, `Component.stories.tsx`, `index.ts`
- **forwardRef**: Use for form controls and focusable elements
- **Base UI**: Button, Checkbox, Switch, Dropdown, Dialog, Tab etc. wrap @base-ui/react
- **Theme**: `useTheme()` → `themeClass`, `clsx(themeClass, styles.xxx(), className)`
- **props**: `className`, `...props` (forward HTML attributes) required

## 4. Tokens & Theming

- **Contract**: `src/tokens/semantic/tokens.css.ts` — `createThemeContract()`
- **Intent**: `primary | secondary | success | warning | danger | neutral`
- **Variant**: `solid | outline | subtle | weak` (per component)
- **Per theme**: `.${gameLightTheme} &`, `.${crayonLightTheme} &` selectors

## 5. Code Style

- **No FC**: Use `const C = (props: Props) => {...}` form
- **Named export**: No default exports
- **Commit**: `feat(Component):`, `fix(Component):`, `docs(Component):`

## 6. Commands

```bash
pnpm run build     # Library build
pnpm run test      # Vitest
pnpm run storybook # Storybook
pnpm run docs      # Docs dev server
pnpm run release   # Publish
```
